<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MORE MEN ARRESTED IN BIRTHDAY BRAWL; 4 NOW ACCUSED IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two more men were arrested Tuesday on suspicion of murder in connection with a 
triple stabbing in Burbank that left one man dead and two others seriously hurt 
in a brawl at a birthday party, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Don Goldberg said Jose Villa, 21, and Noe Ortiz, 31, were arrested at 1 
a.m. Tuesday in the apartment they share in Huntington Park. They were being 
held without bail on suspicion of murder at the Burbank Jail. 
</P>
<P>
Four men have been arrested as a result of the Sunday night incident. Police 
said Teresa Ponce, 53, the woman whose birthday was being celebrated, and 
Marbella Cardenas, 22, were also jailed when investigators found a small amount 
of cocaine in the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
The women, who share the apartment, were arrested on suspicion of possession of 
cocaine and were being held in lieu of $2,500 bail each at the Burbank Jail. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Sunday's party -- involving more than 30 people at an apartment 
complex in the 2300 block of North Ontario Avenue -- turned into a brawl about 
8:30 p.m. During the melee, three neighbors -- David Robles, 25; Audiel 
Gonzalez, 21, and Mario Jovin, 23 -- were stabbed. Robles died at St. Joseph 
Medical Center in Burbank. Gonzalez and Jovin were in serious condition at Los 
Angeles County-USC Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Police called to the apartment complex arrested Ramon Ambriz, 35, and Santiago 
Ponce, 21, Teresa Ponce's son, on suspicion of murder. Both men were also being 
held at the Burbank Jail. 
</P>
<P>
Goldberg said further investigation of the incident led detectives to Villa and 
Ortiz on Tuesday. He said there are no other suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
